# Debian build notes for Lara Nux

This directory is the Debian metadata source for the Ubuntu package, but the
repository intentionally keeps it under `packaging/ubuntu/` instead of polluting
 the repo root.

## Expected build flow

1. Build or collect the release artifacts outside of Debian helpers.
2. Stage them under:
   - `packaging/ubuntu/stage/usr/bin/lara-nuxd`
   - `packaging/ubuntu/stage/usr/lib/lara-nux/client/`
3. Expose this directory as the active `debian/` directory in the build root
   (symlink or copy it at repo root in CI).
4. Run `dpkg-buildpackage -us -uc`.
5. Sign the resulting `.changes` / `.dsc` and publish the `.deb` into the apt
   repository described under `packaging/ubuntu/repo/`.

The maintainer scripts are sourced from `packaging/ubuntu/scripts/` during
`dh_installdeb`, so packaging logic stays centralized and idempotent.
